jQuery
'preserve'
"For a given graph <b>G' = ( V' , E' )</b> and integer <b>k'</b>, the "
"Independent Set problem is to find whether <b>G'</b> contains an Independent Set "
"of size >= <b>k'</b>.<br><br>"
"<b>Reduction of Clique to Independent Set</b><br><br><br>"
"To reduce a Clique Problem to an Independet Set problem for a given "
"graph <b>G = ( V , E )</b>, construct a complimentary graph <b>G' = ( V' , E' "
")</b> such that <br><br>"
"1.  <b>V = V' </b> , i.e. the compliment graph will have the same "
"vertices as the original graph<br><br>"
"2.  <b>E'</b> is the compliment of <b>E</b> i.e. <b>G'</b> has all the "
"edges that is <b>not</b> present in <b>G</b><br><br>"
step
"Note:  Construction of the complimentary graph can be done in "
"polynomial time"
"<b>Example graph</b>"
g

hide
umsg
"<b>Clique problem reduced to Independent Set</b><br><br><br>"
g
"1. <b>If there is an independent set of size k in the complement "
"graph G'</b>, it implies no two vertices share an edge in G' which further "
"implies all of those vertices share an edge with all others in G forming a "
"clique. i.e. <b>there exists a clique of size k in G</b><br><br>"
'preserve'
"2. <b>If there is a clique of size k in the graph G</b>, it implies "
"all vertices share an edge with all others in G which further implies no two of "
"these vertices share an edge in G' forming an Independent Set. i.e. <b>there "
"exists an independent set of size k in G'</b>"
"<b>Does G' below have an independent set of size 8? "
"</b><br><br><br>"
show
"<b>NO</b><br.<br>"
"<b>Does G below have a clique of size 8? </b><br><br><br>"
